    vector calculations: following operations perform calculations on 3d vectors and scalars
        common options:
            --input-fields: print input field names and exit
            --output-fields: print output field names and exit
            --output-format: print output format and exit
    
        corss: calculate vector cross product; output: vector
            input fields: v1, v2
            --v1=<x>,<y>,<z>: default value for vector 1
            --v2=<x>,<y>,<z>: default value for vector 2
        dot: calculate vector dot product; output: scalar
            input fields: v1, v2
            --v1=<x>,<y>,<z>: default value for vector 1
            --v2=<x>,<y>,<z>: default value for vector 2
        norm: calculate vector's norm 
            --v1=<x>,<y>,<z>: default value for vecotr
            --square: calculate norm square
            --invert: calculate invert of norm; use with --square for invert of norm square
        scale: calculate multiplication of scalar and vector;output vector
            input fields: a (scalar), v1
            --v1=<x>,<y>,<z>: default value for vecotr
            --scalar: default value for a
            --invert: invert the scalar first and then multiply it by vecotr, i.e. (1/a)*v1

